# OTP Input — React API

> **Merged into `@acko/text-input`**
> Import: `import { OtpInput } from '@acko/text-input'`
> CSS: included in `@acko/css/text-input.css` — no separate import needed.

## Props
```tsx
interface OtpInputProps {
  value: string;
  onChange: (value: string) => void;
  length?: number;               // default: 6
  disabled?: boolean;            // default: false
  error?: boolean;               // default: false
  size?: 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg';    // default: 'md'
  type?: 'numeric' | 'alphanumeric';  // default: 'numeric'
  masked?: boolean;              // renders as password inputs
  className?: string;
  'aria-label'?: string;         // default: 'One-time password'
}
```

## Behaviour
- Auto-advances focus to next cell on valid input
- Backspace: clears current cell; if empty, moves back and clears previous
- ArrowLeft / ArrowRight: navigate between cells
- Paste: strips invalid chars, distributes across cells, advances focus
- Numeric type: allows only `[0-9]`; alphanumeric: `[a-zA-Z0-9]` (auto-uppercased)
- First cell has `autoComplete="one-time-code"` for SMS OTP autofill
- Group: `role="group"`, each cell `aria-label="Digit N of M"`

## Usage
```tsx
const [otp, setOtp] = useState('');
<OtpInput
  value={otp}
  onChange={setOtp}
  length={6}
  aria-label="Verification code"
/>
```
